Minister of Health, Dr Zweli Mkhize will hold a live Zoom public engagement on Monday. The engagement will focus on technical aspects relating to the country's COVID-19 response. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Health Dr Zweli Mkhize will hold a live Zoom public engagement on Monday. The engagement will focus on technical aspects relating to the country's COVID-19 response. WATCH: DA delivers its COVID-19 strategy This meeting will also be joined by experts on COVID-19. The number of confirmed cases in South Africa is 2,173 and 25 people have died as a result of COVID-19. The lockdown has been extended as South Africa tries to contain the spread of COVID-19.